Allan Cardy (born in Katoomba, NSW) was a representative of Australia in rugby union. Captain of Katoomba High School in 1962, he played for the Drummoyne club in Sydney before switching to other rugby code  rugby league in 1969. However his wing-threequarters career never reached any great heightd in rugby league after suffering a broken leg in the pre-season.

